      <subsection>
        <title>Practice 3: Apply Division Algorithm</title>
        <p>
          <row><alert>Theorem: The Division Algorithm (for Integers)</alert></row>
          Let <m>a</m> by an integer and <m>b</m> be a natural number. Then there <em>exists unique</em> integers <m>q</m> and <m>r</m> such that
          <me>
            a=q\cdot b+r, \text{where }\qquad 0 \leq r < b.
          </me>
          The integer <m>q</m> is called the <alert>quotient</alert> and the value <m>r</m> is called the <alert>remainder</alert>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <setup>
            <selectFromSequence from="19" to="20" name="a"/>
            <selectFromSequence from="6" to="8" name="b" />
          </setup>
          <row><alert>Examples</alert></row>
          Suppose that <m>a=$a,b=$b</m>. Then we can write
          <me>
            $a = <math simplify>floor($a/$b)</math>\cdot $b + <math simplify>mod($a,$b)</math>.
          </me>
          Note that the remainders can be zero, as in the case <m>a=15, b=5</m>, in which case we have:
          <me>
            15 = 3\cdot 5 + 0.
          </me>
        </p>
        <setup>
          <selectFromSequence name="a2" from="10" to="13" />
          <selectFromSequence name="b2" from="7" to="9" />
          <selectFromSequence name="a3" from="40" to="80" step="4" />
          <selectFromSequence name="b3" from="11" to="19" step="2" />
          <selectFromSequence name="a4" from="18" to="81" step="9" />
          <selectFromSequence name="b4" from="3" to="9" step="6" />
          <selectFromSequence name="a5" from="2" to="8" step="2" />
          <selectFromSequence name="b5" from="30" to="50" />
          <selectFromSequence name="a6" from="20" to="29" step="2" exclude="24" />
        </setup>
        <p>
          <row><alert>Practice Problems</alert></row>
          For each of the following, compute the quotient and remainder for the division algorithm.
          <tabular>
            <copy tname="divAlg" A="$a2" B="$b2" />
            <copy tname="divAlg" A="$a3" B="$b3" />
            <copy tname="divAlg" A="$a4" B="$b4" />
            <copy tname="divAlg" A="$a5" B="$b5" />
            <copy tname="divAlg" A="-$a6" B="3" />
          </tabular>
        </p>
